  <h2 id="benefits">Benefits of Centrifuge-Based Black Diesel Production</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sub-micron particle separation:</strong> Removes metallic wear particles down to <strong>0.5 microns</strong> &mdash; critical for protecting injectors and combustion chambers</li>
    <li><strong>Large processing capacity:</strong> Systems available up to <strong>80 GPM</strong>, suitable for commercial-scale production</li>
    <li><strong>Complete water separation:</strong> Removes all free and emulsified water, preventing corrosion and combustion issues</li>
    <li><strong>Low operating cost:</strong> No consumable filter elements; primary cost is electricity for the drive motor</li>
    <li><strong>Compact footprint:</strong> A 20 GPM centrifuge system occupies approximately 4' &times; 5' of floor space</li>
    <li><strong>Ash removal:</strong> Centrifugal force separates calcium, zinc, and phosphorus ash compounds that cause deposit buildup</li>
    <li><strong>Emulsion breaking:</strong> High G-force breaks oil-water emulsions that settle tanks and coalescing filters cannot separate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="limitations">Limitations</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Capital cost:</strong> Industrial disc stack centrifuges represent a significant upfront investment compared to basic filtration equipment</li>
    <li><strong>Maintenance requirements:</strong> Centrifuges require periodic maintenance including bowl cleaning, seal replacement, and bearing inspection</li>
    <li><strong>Skilled operation:</strong> Proper setup and adjustment requires trained operators who understand separation principles, gravity disc sizing, and feed temperature control</li>
    <li><strong>Utility requirements:</strong> Systems need three-phase power (typically 460V) and may require steam or electric pre-heaters to reduce oil viscosity for optimal separation</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Despite these considerations, the centrifuge's ability to produce consistently clean fuel from highly contaminated feedstock makes it the preferred technology for serious black diesel operations.
  </p>

